inclusion.label: met
inclusion.evidence: The patient is a 20 year old Caucasian female presents to the clinic with one-sided vision lost and facial weakness, dysarthria and numbness lasting for 1 day.

exclusion.label: triggers
exclusion.evidence: The patient is under the treatment of RRMS from 7 months ago.

notes: The patient has a history of Relapsing Remitting Multiple Sclerosis (RRMS) and is currently under treatment. She also smokes 10 cigarettes per day.
